1
00:01:36,470 --> 00:01:38,990
[A Love Never Lost]

2
00:01:40,520 --> 00:01:42,020
[Episode 29]

3
00:01:43,150 --> 00:01:44,200
Kaizhi,

4
00:01:45,640 --> 00:01:47,509
a woman lived with a man

5
00:01:48,789 --> 00:01:50,280
for so long,

6
00:01:51,479 --> 00:01:52,280
and yet she didn't know

7
00:01:52,280 --> 00:01:54,070
why she needed him so much.

8
00:01:55,560 --> 00:01:57,560
It's like a fish living in water,

9
00:01:57,710 --> 00:01:59,070
never once asking

10
00:01:59,479 --> 00:02:00,540
what water even is.

11
00:02:02,590 --> 00:02:03,920
She never thought about

12
00:02:04,070 --> 00:02:05,120
goals,

13
00:02:05,400 --> 00:02:06,200
beliefs,

14
00:02:07,230 --> 00:02:08,400
or ideals

15
00:02:09,060 --> 00:02:09,900
because that person

16
00:02:09,900 --> 00:02:11,900
made almost every decision for you.

17
00:02:13,150 --> 00:02:14,870
She took his dreams as her own,

18
00:02:15,750 --> 00:02:17,150
his goals as her goals,

19
00:02:17,870 --> 00:02:19,670
his victories as her victories,

20
00:02:20,110 --> 00:02:21,850
and his honors as her honors.

21
00:02:30,870 --> 00:02:32,079
I get it.

22
00:02:33,960 --> 00:02:35,360
Until one day,

23
00:02:36,870 --> 00:02:38,240
she lost him,

24
00:02:39,800 --> 00:02:41,400
and only then did she realize

25
00:02:42,360 --> 00:02:43,870
she had no idea where to go.

26
00:02:46,590 --> 00:02:48,590
There's this emptiness inside her,

27
00:02:49,710 --> 00:02:51,440
like everything left with him.

28
00:02:54,870 --> 00:02:55,810
You understand?

29
00:03:00,150 --> 00:03:01,080
I do.

30
00:03:03,590 --> 00:03:05,080
But I also don't.

31
00:03:08,360 --> 00:03:09,710
How could one person…

32
00:03:10,870 --> 00:03:11,800
completely replace

33
00:03:11,800 --> 00:03:13,080
another person?

34
00:03:14,960 --> 00:03:16,030
Whatever the case,

35
00:03:16,870 --> 00:03:18,630
what you did in Tokyo—

36
00:03:19,240 --> 00:03:20,370
not every woman

37
00:03:20,770 --> 00:03:21,980
could've done that.

38
00:03:23,310 --> 00:03:24,430
I don't believe

39
00:03:25,190 --> 00:03:27,430
you were just brainwashed by someone else.

40
00:03:27,430 --> 00:03:28,360
It's simple.

41
00:03:28,710 --> 00:03:30,170
I had to survive, didn't I?

42
00:03:33,150 --> 00:03:34,310
That is belief.

43
00:03:38,150 --> 00:03:39,240
That's belief?

44
00:03:39,520 --> 00:03:40,150
Of course.

45
00:03:40,690 --> 00:03:41,520
Shuhong,

46
00:03:42,079 --> 00:03:43,480
I know how deeply it hurts

47
00:03:43,520 --> 00:03:45,000
to lose the one you love.

48
00:03:45,630 --> 00:03:47,560
But this is not the end of the world.

49
00:03:48,010 --> 00:03:48,880
I believe

50
00:03:49,150 --> 00:03:50,310
humans won't

51
00:03:50,310 --> 00:03:51,360
just scrape by;

52
00:03:51,520 --> 00:03:53,079
they'll thrive.

53
00:03:53,400 --> 00:03:55,060
Humanity is not meant to fade.

54
00:03:55,800 --> 00:03:56,870
That's belief.

55
00:05:12,510 --> 00:05:13,400
Mother,

56
00:05:14,030 --> 00:05:15,380
why are you still up?

57
00:05:21,190 --> 00:05:23,450
Why'd you put the turtle in the fishbowl?

58
00:05:27,190 --> 00:05:29,160
Look at the goldfish.

59
00:05:29,720 --> 00:05:31,580
They're not afraid of the turtle.

60
00:05:32,000 --> 00:05:33,730
That turtle's got a wide shell,

61
00:05:33,870 --> 00:05:35,630
but it's slow and clumsy.

62
00:05:35,870 --> 00:05:36,630
Look at it.

63
00:05:39,430 --> 00:05:40,430
Where's that boy?

64
00:05:40,630 --> 00:05:42,190
Where's the boy at Kaizhi's place?

65
00:05:42,190 --> 00:05:43,650
Duo Mei, go bring him over.

66
00:05:43,750 --> 00:05:44,880
Mother is too bored.

67
00:05:52,190 --> 00:05:53,500
Bring him over?

68
00:05:55,159 --> 00:05:56,480
His mother came back

69
00:05:56,720 --> 00:05:57,720
and took him home.

70
00:05:58,800 --> 00:05:59,920
Is that so?

71
00:06:00,360 --> 00:06:01,360
That explains it.

72
00:06:02,000 --> 00:06:02,510
Come on.

73
00:06:02,920 --> 00:06:03,480
Mother,

74
00:06:03,800 --> 00:06:05,630
let's have a chat.

75
00:06:06,190 --> 00:06:07,890
With that boozy breath?

76
00:06:07,920 --> 00:06:09,310
Chat my foot.

77
00:06:09,630 --> 00:06:10,960
Go wash up and get to bed.

78
00:06:12,430 --> 00:06:13,720
We're turning in too.

79
00:06:14,310 --> 00:06:15,070
Jianqiu,

80
00:06:15,480 --> 00:06:16,920
is the foot bath ready?

81
00:06:17,190 --> 00:06:18,120
Yes, it's ready.

82
00:06:28,510 --> 00:06:29,870
Tufang, the boy at Kaizhi's place…

83
00:06:29,870 --> 00:06:30,720
Duo Mei.

84
00:06:30,920 --> 00:06:31,570
Come.

85
00:06:40,480 --> 00:06:41,190
Where is he?

86
00:06:41,800 --> 00:06:42,860
Right in this room.

87
00:06:48,430 --> 00:06:49,240
Second Lord.

88
00:06:49,800 --> 00:06:51,600
Director Yang, why did you

89
00:06:51,700 --> 00:06:52,870
invite me here?

90
00:06:54,650 --> 00:06:55,920
Can't we just have a meal together?

91
00:06:55,920 --> 00:06:56,480
No.

92
00:06:56,900 --> 00:06:58,760
What's there to eat at Douhua Restaurant?

93
00:06:58,760 --> 00:07:00,490
If you've got business, say it.

94
00:07:05,000 --> 00:07:05,430
Hey.

95
00:07:06,430 --> 00:07:07,070
Go to the carriage

96
00:07:07,070 --> 00:07:08,390
and take those two pups

97
00:07:08,450 --> 00:07:10,160
to the Japanese legation.

98
00:07:10,920 --> 00:07:11,310
Go.

99
00:07:12,730 --> 00:07:14,650
Liang's been asking me
to do that for half a month.

100
00:07:14,650 --> 00:07:16,170
Said they have to be delivered

101
00:07:16,170 --> 00:07:17,970
to the military attaché's wife.

102
00:07:18,320 --> 00:07:19,650
They're for Ms. Yoshiko,

103
00:07:19,650 --> 00:07:21,170
the wife of Attaché Hirata, right?

104
00:07:21,170 --> 00:07:21,930
Her father

105
00:07:22,200 --> 00:07:24,130
is from the Japanese royal family.

106
00:07:25,650 --> 00:07:27,050
I almost forgot.

107
00:07:27,200 --> 00:07:28,050
Kaizhi.

108
00:07:28,490 --> 00:07:30,050
You studied in Japan too, didn't you?

109
00:07:30,050 --> 00:07:31,530
I heard you and Liang

110
00:07:31,530 --> 00:07:32,930
had beds side by side.

111
00:07:33,320 --> 00:07:34,050
That's true.

112
00:07:34,270 --> 00:07:35,760
Then why are you asking me for help?

113
00:07:35,760 --> 00:07:37,530
If there's something,
go talk to Liang Xiang.

114
00:07:37,530 --> 00:07:38,090
The Prince Regent,

115
00:07:38,090 --> 00:07:39,920
by the imperial edict
from the Xuantong Emperor,

116
00:07:39,920 --> 00:07:41,730
has consolidated
military power under himself,

117
00:07:41,730 --> 00:07:43,760
acting as Commander-in-Chief
of both the Army and Navy.

118
00:07:43,760 --> 00:07:45,090
His two blood brothers—

119
00:07:45,610 --> 00:07:47,470
one's been made Minister of Navy,

120
00:07:47,490 --> 00:07:49,930
the other Chairman
of the Military Advisory Council,

121
00:07:49,930 --> 00:07:51,610
and he's in charge
of the Imperial Guards too.

122
00:07:51,610 --> 00:07:52,670
Those three people

123
00:07:53,050 --> 00:07:54,240
know nothing at all.

124
00:07:54,930 --> 00:07:56,610
Military orders
and telegrams about military affairs

125
00:07:56,610 --> 00:07:57,490
are all

126
00:07:57,490 --> 00:07:58,880
handled by Liang.

127
00:08:04,050 --> 00:08:05,170
Tufang is the one

128
00:08:05,490 --> 00:08:07,020
who asked me to come see you.

129
00:08:07,730 --> 00:08:09,050
He sent you to me?

130
00:08:09,360 --> 00:08:10,090
Second Lord.

131
00:08:10,650 --> 00:08:11,610
I'm a soldier.

132
00:08:11,760 --> 00:08:12,730
I speak plainly.

133
00:08:13,050 --> 00:08:14,050
I invited you here

134
00:08:14,320 --> 00:08:15,380
for just one thing:

135
00:08:16,160 --> 00:08:17,360
to deliver something

136
00:08:17,650 --> 00:08:18,510
to your father.

137
00:08:19,200 --> 00:08:20,240
There it is.

138
00:08:21,240 --> 00:08:22,760
I was wondering
why the Border Defense Hero

139
00:08:22,760 --> 00:08:23,650
of the court

140
00:08:23,650 --> 00:08:25,320
wanted to have dinner with me.

141
00:08:25,650 --> 00:08:26,090
No.

142
00:08:26,440 --> 00:08:27,440
Please let me finish.

143
00:08:27,440 --> 00:08:28,000
Don't.

144
00:08:28,170 --> 00:08:29,430
I don't want to hear it.

145
00:08:29,440 --> 00:08:31,390
My father is my father, and I am me.

146
00:08:31,410 --> 00:08:32,600
If you want something, go to him directly.

147
00:08:32,600 --> 00:08:33,169
Don't come to me.

148
00:08:33,169 --> 00:08:35,500
Besides, he wouldn't listen to me anyway.

149
00:08:35,600 --> 00:08:36,330
Second Lord.

150
00:08:37,080 --> 00:08:38,610
You don't need to say a word.

151
00:08:38,940 --> 00:08:40,740
Just pass along one thing for me.

152
00:08:56,320 --> 00:08:57,770
Well,

153
00:08:58,200 --> 00:08:59,530
you owe my father money?

154
00:09:00,920 --> 00:09:01,720
That's right.

155
00:09:02,320 --> 00:09:03,320
After all, he holds the power

156
00:09:03,320 --> 00:09:04,850
to decide the life and death

157
00:09:04,890 --> 00:09:06,750
of a low-ranking officer like me.

158
00:09:06,890 --> 00:09:08,770
But my father is no longer

159
00:09:08,770 --> 00:09:10,650
the Chief Grand Council Minister.

160
00:09:10,650 --> 00:09:11,290
No.

161
00:09:11,650 --> 00:09:12,650
In my opinion,

162
00:09:13,080 --> 00:09:16,080
once a leader, always a leader.

163
00:09:16,960 --> 00:09:17,840
Not just for me—

164
00:09:18,320 --> 00:09:20,180
even for Empress Dowager Longyu,

165
00:09:20,290 --> 00:09:22,010
her title and status back then

166
00:09:22,200 --> 00:09:23,320
were something your father

167
00:09:23,320 --> 00:09:24,680
helped secure

168
00:09:24,890 --> 00:09:26,200
from the late Empress Dowager.

169
00:09:26,200 --> 00:09:27,200
Isn't that right?

170
00:09:27,530 --> 00:09:28,440
For that alone,

171
00:09:28,890 --> 00:09:29,890
the Prince Regent

172
00:09:30,080 --> 00:09:32,340
should show some respect to your father.

173
00:09:35,010 --> 00:09:35,890
Today,

174
00:09:36,080 --> 00:09:38,560
I've finally met someone who gets it.

175
00:09:40,010 --> 00:09:40,530
Sit.

176
00:09:41,200 --> 00:09:42,200
I do get it.

177
00:09:42,770 --> 00:09:45,050
If I'm to help someone,

178
00:09:45,200 --> 00:09:46,770
I only help those who get me.

179
00:09:47,080 --> 00:09:48,410
Helping clueless fools

180
00:09:48,440 --> 00:09:50,410
is a waste of effort and thankless.

181
00:09:50,890 --> 00:09:53,770
That bunch of dimwits
knows nothing at all,

182
00:09:54,010 --> 00:09:55,410
always begging for help,

183
00:09:55,410 --> 00:09:56,960
like my father's some public toilet

184
00:09:56,960 --> 00:09:58,890
anyone can use.

185
00:09:59,010 --> 00:09:59,840
And it's always over

186
00:09:59,840 --> 00:10:01,320
the pettiest and nastiest problems.

187
00:10:01,320 --> 00:10:02,530
Ridiculous.

188
00:10:02,650 --> 00:10:03,890
What I want is simple.

189
00:10:04,890 --> 00:10:05,840
I believe

190
00:10:06,010 --> 00:10:08,410
I have the ability and qualifications

191
00:10:09,080 --> 00:10:11,080
to lead the Sixth Beiyang Division.

192
00:10:13,840 --> 00:10:15,650
That final line I said

193
00:10:15,890 --> 00:10:16,890
was so badass!

194
00:10:18,530 --> 00:10:19,410
With that 30,000 yuan

195
00:10:19,410 --> 00:10:20,530
right under his nose,

196
00:10:20,530 --> 00:10:22,440
it didn't really matter what you said.

197
00:10:22,440 --> 00:10:23,130
No.

198
00:10:23,650 --> 00:10:24,580
The point is that

199
00:10:24,650 --> 00:10:26,510
I was so confident and righteous.

200
00:10:28,650 --> 00:10:30,050
Sounds like a trade to me.

201
00:10:31,010 --> 00:10:32,200
You're not wrong.

202
00:10:33,010 --> 00:10:34,070
But if it's a trade,

203
00:10:34,080 --> 00:10:34,530
you shouldn't have

204
00:10:34,530 --> 00:10:36,320
thrown all your money
on the table at once.

205
00:10:36,320 --> 00:10:38,120
That puts you in a weak position.

206
00:10:38,130 --> 00:10:40,060
You've left yourself no leverage.

207
00:10:40,560 --> 00:10:42,020
That's exactly the point!

208
00:10:42,200 --> 00:10:43,010
What if he thinks

209
00:10:43,010 --> 00:10:43,940
it's not enough?

210
00:10:44,530 --> 00:10:45,860
How can it be not enough?

211
00:10:45,960 --> 00:10:47,890
If it's a trade,
there's always price negotiation.

212
00:10:47,890 --> 00:10:49,490
Haggling is part of the game.

213
00:10:49,530 --> 00:10:50,200
No,

214
00:10:53,200 --> 00:10:54,320
this isn't a trade.

215
00:10:54,680 --> 00:10:55,890
It's a gamble.

216
00:10:56,440 --> 00:10:57,680
I've put

217
00:10:58,080 --> 00:10:59,410
all my money on the table,

218
00:10:59,410 --> 00:11:01,010
so it's not my money anymore.

219
00:11:04,010 --> 00:11:05,810
You two are surprisingly alike.

220
00:11:06,550 --> 00:11:07,680
You mean Wu Tianbai?

221
00:11:08,200 --> 00:11:09,320
That's right.

222
00:11:10,200 --> 00:11:11,770
That kind of
small-stakes thinking of yours

223
00:11:11,770 --> 00:11:13,030
will ruin everything.

224
00:11:13,320 --> 00:11:14,450
With that attitude,

225
00:11:14,650 --> 00:11:15,770
you think they'll hand

226
00:11:15,770 --> 00:11:17,290
the Beiyang Army's main force over to you?

227
00:11:17,290 --> 00:11:18,320
Am I right, Bugu?

228
00:11:19,530 --> 00:11:20,410
Sounds like

229
00:11:20,530 --> 00:11:21,730
you make a good point.

230
00:11:22,080 --> 00:11:22,890
So…

231
00:11:23,010 --> 00:11:24,320
For a trade this big,

232
00:11:24,650 --> 00:11:26,320
you can't push from only one side.

233
00:11:26,320 --> 00:11:27,920
You need Liang Xiang's help.

234
00:11:28,410 --> 00:11:30,010
We all need help from others.

235
00:11:30,130 --> 00:11:31,890
Don't be too reserved with Liang Xiang.

236
00:11:31,890 --> 00:11:33,680
He's already the reserved type.

237
00:11:33,680 --> 00:11:35,140
You two are a bit too alike,

238
00:11:35,770 --> 00:11:37,200
both trying to keep your hands clean.

239
00:11:37,200 --> 00:11:37,890
But this whole thing

240
00:11:37,890 --> 00:11:39,350
isn't clean to begin with.

241
00:11:42,890 --> 00:11:43,960
Exactly.

242
00:11:44,770 --> 00:11:46,380
That's why the way I do things…

243
00:11:46,380 --> 00:11:47,580
Alright. Go back now.

244
00:11:47,770 --> 00:11:49,230
I've aired out your quilt.

245
00:12:12,200 --> 00:12:12,890
Bugu.

246
00:12:13,200 --> 00:12:14,530
Bring me your dirty laundry.

247
00:12:14,530 --> 00:12:15,990
Mommy will wash it for you.

248
00:12:17,080 --> 00:12:17,890
Good boy.

249
00:12:20,010 --> 00:12:21,540
Don't get your sleeves wet.

250
00:12:42,770 --> 00:12:44,770
Oh, don't spill the water.

251
00:12:45,010 --> 00:12:45,890
Be good.

252
00:12:46,080 --> 00:12:48,770
I almost plunged headfirst into the water.

253
00:13:04,810 --> 00:13:06,210
Look at how I wash it.

254
00:13:09,320 --> 00:13:09,820
Bugu,

255
00:13:09,890 --> 00:13:10,490
come here.

256
00:13:13,330 --> 00:13:14,560
Give this to your mom.

257
00:13:18,560 --> 00:13:19,690
I forgot to tell you.

258
00:13:19,890 --> 00:13:21,420
There's soap on my cabinet.

259
00:13:21,510 --> 00:13:22,150
It helps

260
00:13:22,290 --> 00:13:23,410
a lot.

261
00:13:24,130 --> 00:13:24,860
Sleep early.

262
00:13:25,000 --> 00:13:26,120
Go back now.

263
00:13:27,080 --> 00:13:27,650
Bugu.

264
00:13:28,010 --> 00:13:28,650
Bugu.

265
00:13:28,870 --> 00:13:29,600
I'm leaving.

266
00:13:46,870 --> 00:13:56,080
[Military Advisory Council]

267
00:14:00,360 --> 00:14:01,160
Shift change.

268
00:14:09,440 --> 00:14:10,200
Tufang,

269
00:14:10,560 --> 00:14:12,440
I don't think it's a good idea.

270
00:14:12,650 --> 00:14:15,010
Why insist on
wearing the Beiyang Army's uniforms?

271
00:14:15,010 --> 00:14:17,670
The Imperial Guards' uniforms
look way better.

272
00:14:18,320 --> 00:14:19,410
The Military Advisory Council

273
00:14:19,410 --> 00:14:21,200
commands the entire army of the country.

274
00:14:21,200 --> 00:14:23,650
If you only wear
the Imperial Guard uniform,

275
00:14:23,650 --> 00:14:26,250
it'll look like
you've got limited authority.

276
00:14:26,440 --> 00:14:28,300
Wearing the Beiyang Army uniform

277
00:14:28,320 --> 00:14:29,680
reaffirms the Military Advisory Council's

278
00:14:29,680 --> 00:14:31,540
authority over elite army units.

279
00:14:33,680 --> 00:14:34,530
Fair point.

280
00:14:35,440 --> 00:14:36,200
Let's go.

281
00:14:36,440 --> 00:14:37,650
Time to see

282
00:14:37,650 --> 00:14:38,530
your command room

283
00:14:38,530 --> 00:14:39,460
as the Chairman.

284
00:14:58,890 --> 00:14:59,770
Well?

285
00:15:00,080 --> 00:15:01,010
Do I look like

286
00:15:01,130 --> 00:15:02,200
the Qing Army's

287
00:15:02,200 --> 00:15:03,730
Chief of the General Staff?

288
00:15:04,440 --> 00:15:06,370
Just looking like it isn't enough.

289
00:15:09,010 --> 00:15:10,770
Then what should I do?

290
00:15:11,440 --> 00:15:12,530
Three words:

291
00:15:13,080 --> 00:15:14,410
control the troops.

292
00:15:18,080 --> 00:15:19,940
Where do all these lines connect?

293
00:15:22,410 --> 00:15:23,200
This one

294
00:15:23,440 --> 00:15:26,170
goes directly
to the Prince Regent's residence.

295
00:15:26,200 --> 00:15:27,010
This one

296
00:15:27,080 --> 00:15:28,530
to the six Beiyang Divisions.

297
00:15:28,530 --> 00:15:29,960
And this one here

298
00:15:30,200 --> 00:15:30,770
goes directly to

299
00:15:30,770 --> 00:15:34,300
the Imperial Guards' Training Department.
I just moved there.

300
00:15:40,530 --> 00:15:41,410
Who is it?

301
00:15:41,840 --> 00:15:42,650
Zaifeng.

302
00:15:43,010 --> 00:15:44,200
It's me, Zaitao.

303
00:15:44,770 --> 00:15:45,650
Yes, yes, yes.

304
00:15:45,970 --> 00:15:47,930
I've arrived
at my Military Advisory Council,

305
00:15:47,930 --> 00:15:49,650
and I'm formally reporting to you:

306
00:15:49,650 --> 00:15:50,530
as of today,

307
00:15:50,650 --> 00:15:52,530
we are officially in operation.

308
00:15:54,680 --> 00:15:55,410
What?

309
00:15:55,680 --> 00:15:57,440
You're talking to Zhang Jian?

310
00:15:57,890 --> 00:15:58,890
Who is Zhang Jian?

311
00:16:02,360 --> 00:16:02,820
He says…

312
00:16:02,840 --> 00:16:03,890
Zhang Jian is the leading figure

313
00:16:03,890 --> 00:16:05,650
of the southern constitutionalists.

314
00:16:05,650 --> 00:16:07,290
How could you not know him?

315
00:16:08,440 --> 00:16:10,170
Zhang Jian, Li Jian, whatever.

316
00:16:10,320 --> 00:16:11,650
Not even a word of congratulations

317
00:16:11,650 --> 00:16:12,290
from him.

318
00:16:12,650 --> 00:16:13,680
Buzzkill.

319
00:16:15,890 --> 00:16:17,290
The constitutionalists

320
00:16:17,320 --> 00:16:19,410
are a real headache
for the court right now.

321
00:16:19,410 --> 00:16:19,890
Zhang Jian

322
00:16:19,890 --> 00:16:21,950
was even once Yuan Shikai's teacher.

323
00:16:22,080 --> 00:16:23,200
Even so,

324
00:16:23,770 --> 00:16:24,840
the Prince Regent personally

325
00:16:24,840 --> 00:16:26,410
received him, trying to win him over.

326
00:16:26,410 --> 00:16:27,440
It's a wise move

327
00:16:27,650 --> 00:16:28,890
that shows vision.

328
00:16:30,960 --> 00:16:32,530
Where were we just now?

329
00:16:33,080 --> 00:16:34,210
Control the troops?

330
00:16:34,650 --> 00:16:35,650
How?

331
00:16:36,080 --> 00:16:37,200
Two words:

332
00:16:37,890 --> 00:16:38,680
use people.

333
00:16:41,200 --> 00:16:42,770
I want to appoint people,

334
00:16:43,200 --> 00:16:44,770
but I don't get a say.

335
00:16:45,680 --> 00:16:46,290
Do you know who

336
00:16:46,290 --> 00:16:47,010
Prince Qing

337
00:16:47,010 --> 00:16:49,560
nominated yesterday
as commander of the Sixth Division?

338
00:16:49,560 --> 00:16:51,080
You'll never guess.

339
00:16:52,200 --> 00:16:52,730
Who?

340
00:16:53,530 --> 00:16:54,960
Your old classmate,

341
00:16:55,200 --> 00:16:56,500
Yang Kaizhi.

342
00:17:00,200 --> 00:17:01,730
Do you think he's a good fit?

343
00:17:03,200 --> 00:17:04,460
This time, Prince Qing

344
00:17:04,650 --> 00:17:05,780
made the right call.

345
00:17:06,680 --> 00:17:08,130
I don't think so.

346
00:17:08,690 --> 00:17:10,260
Someone reported to me

347
00:17:10,650 --> 00:17:12,890
that Yang Kaizhi has a
questionable background.

348
00:17:12,890 --> 00:17:14,200
He had close contact

349
00:17:14,200 --> 00:17:16,410
with rebels back in Tokyo.

350
00:17:19,569 --> 00:17:20,250
Is that so?

351
00:17:26,410 --> 00:17:27,569
Tufang.

352
00:17:29,040 --> 00:17:30,520
In this matter,

353
00:17:31,330 --> 00:17:33,530
you don't have a personal stake, do you?

354
00:17:35,500 --> 00:17:38,340
Tokyo is a mixed bag.

355
00:17:38,760 --> 00:17:39,890
There are all kinds

356
00:17:39,890 --> 00:17:41,410
of people there.

357
00:17:42,280 --> 00:17:43,510
Everyone is an acquaintance.

358
00:17:43,510 --> 00:17:45,570
It's impossible to avoid each other.

359
00:17:45,570 --> 00:17:46,590
I'm the same.

360
00:17:47,520 --> 00:17:48,520
Truth be told,

361
00:17:48,810 --> 00:17:50,440
even ringleaders

362
00:17:50,440 --> 00:17:51,840
like Qiu Jin and Xu Xilin—

363
00:17:52,330 --> 00:17:53,930
I've crossed paths with them

364
00:17:54,040 --> 00:17:55,500
at social events in Tokyo.

365
00:17:55,930 --> 00:17:57,170
By this standard,

366
00:17:59,040 --> 00:18:00,040
are you gonna

367
00:18:00,040 --> 00:18:01,280
stop trusting me too?

368
00:18:02,170 --> 00:18:02,760
No.

369
00:18:03,890 --> 00:18:04,520
No, no.

370
00:18:05,520 --> 00:18:07,330
How could I not trust you?

371
00:18:07,760 --> 00:18:09,760
If I don't trust you, who can I trust?

372
00:18:10,330 --> 00:18:11,990
You're not like them, Tufang.

373
00:18:12,000 --> 00:18:13,410
Before you left for Tokyo,

374
00:18:13,410 --> 00:18:14,040
when you were in Shanghai,

375
00:18:14,040 --> 00:18:15,970
Zaifeng already had his eye on you.

376
00:18:16,520 --> 00:18:17,810
Among all the Bannermen,

377
00:18:17,810 --> 00:18:19,930
you're the one who's down-to-earth

378
00:18:20,040 --> 00:18:22,170
and stays true to our ancestral teachings.

379
00:18:22,170 --> 00:18:23,040
If you brothers

380
00:18:23,040 --> 00:18:24,410
trust me,

381
00:18:24,570 --> 00:18:25,650
then you should trust

382
00:18:25,650 --> 00:18:26,580
Yang Kaizhi too.

383
00:18:27,090 --> 00:18:29,290
He has the makings of a great commander.

384
00:18:29,330 --> 00:18:31,170
Leaving him stuck in the Ministry of War

385
00:18:31,170 --> 00:18:33,030
drafting regulations is a waste.

386
00:18:34,040 --> 00:18:34,890
Fine, fine.

387
00:18:35,410 --> 00:18:36,150
I'll pass

388
00:18:36,180 --> 00:18:37,830
your words to Zaifeng.

389
00:18:39,410 --> 00:18:40,280
But

390
00:18:40,280 --> 00:18:41,900
what decision he makes

391
00:18:42,200 --> 00:18:43,750
might be beyond me.

392
00:18:44,760 --> 00:18:45,650
To be honest,

393
00:18:46,930 --> 00:18:48,590
being in such a high position,

394
00:18:49,570 --> 00:18:50,890
Zaifeng

395
00:18:50,890 --> 00:18:52,760
isn't the same man he used to be.

396
00:18:53,930 --> 00:18:54,810
These days I barely get to

397
00:18:54,810 --> 00:18:56,210
see him even twice a week.

398
00:18:56,520 --> 00:18:57,440
Historically,

399
00:18:57,440 --> 00:18:59,170
the Beiyang Army's commanders

400
00:18:59,520 --> 00:19:00,520
have all been

401
00:19:00,520 --> 00:19:03,090
fast-track grads
of the Beiyang Military Academy.

402
00:19:03,090 --> 00:19:04,350
It's time for a change.

403
00:19:05,200 --> 00:19:06,200
Cadets trained in Japan

404
00:19:06,200 --> 00:19:08,000
will gradually replace

405
00:19:08,000 --> 00:19:09,280
the old-school officers.

406
00:19:09,280 --> 00:19:10,880
That's the tide of the times.

407
00:19:14,650 --> 00:19:16,510
If all the cadets trained in Japan

408
00:19:16,650 --> 00:19:18,330
were like you, Tufang,

409
00:19:18,810 --> 00:19:20,650
why wouldn't we welcome them?

410
00:19:21,680 --> 00:19:23,040
If you think that way,

411
00:19:23,040 --> 00:19:24,040
I can rest easy.

412
00:19:24,890 --> 00:19:25,650
People

413
00:19:25,930 --> 00:19:26,760
don't become great

414
00:19:26,760 --> 00:19:27,930
overnight.

415
00:19:28,930 --> 00:19:30,530
I understand this very well.

416
00:19:31,090 --> 00:19:32,490
Winning people's hearts

417
00:19:32,570 --> 00:19:34,930
takes time and effort.

418
00:19:36,650 --> 00:19:38,040
I already have a plan.

419
00:19:39,170 --> 00:19:41,040
I'll bring in a few alumni I know well

420
00:19:41,040 --> 00:19:42,410
to be trainee staff officers

421
00:19:42,410 --> 00:19:44,340
at the Military Advisory Council.

422
00:19:44,410 --> 00:19:45,570
We'll test the waters first

423
00:19:45,570 --> 00:19:47,430
and pick the good ones to promote.

424
00:19:49,680 --> 00:19:53,230
[Reunion of Cadets Trained in Japan]

425
00:20:04,520 --> 00:20:05,570
Fang Zhen.

426
00:20:06,200 --> 00:20:06,680
Here.

427
00:20:06,680 --> 00:20:07,330
Okay.

428
00:20:11,330 --> 00:20:12,680
Have you found a job yet?

429
00:20:12,680 --> 00:20:13,280
No.

430
00:20:13,280 --> 00:20:14,880
Still loitering in Beijing.

431
00:20:16,410 --> 00:20:17,890
You, a top student of the third term,

432
00:20:17,890 --> 00:20:18,820
can't find a job?

433
00:20:19,170 --> 00:20:20,410
I wish I could.

434
00:20:21,280 --> 00:20:23,570
Would you consider
joining the Imperial Guards?

435
00:20:23,570 --> 00:20:24,680
We're currently

436
00:20:24,680 --> 00:20:25,930
recruiting talent,

437
00:20:25,930 --> 00:20:26,810
expanding units,

438
00:20:26,810 --> 00:20:28,410
and upgrading our firearms.

439
00:20:29,040 --> 00:20:29,570
Kaizhi.

440
00:20:29,680 --> 00:20:30,170
No.

441
00:20:30,760 --> 00:20:31,930
Director Yang.

442
00:20:33,280 --> 00:20:35,930
I heard the New Army's
organization outline calls for

443
00:20:35,930 --> 00:20:37,040
establishing

444
00:20:37,040 --> 00:20:38,090
18 cavalry brigades

445
00:20:38,090 --> 00:20:40,290
across 18 provinces in the next decade.

446
00:20:41,410 --> 00:20:42,210
That's right.

447
00:20:42,680 --> 00:20:43,890
One per province.

448
00:20:44,040 --> 00:20:45,570
What a big plan.

449
00:20:46,280 --> 00:20:46,810
Yeah.

450
00:20:47,410 --> 00:20:48,410
Quite ambitious.

451
00:20:49,040 --> 00:20:49,900
Send my regards

452
00:20:50,040 --> 00:20:52,650
to your cavalry brigades.

453
00:20:53,170 --> 00:20:54,090
Don't mock me.

454
00:20:54,440 --> 00:20:56,300
Heaven knows where they even are.

455
00:20:59,760 --> 00:21:00,930
Guys, guys.

456
00:21:01,040 --> 00:21:02,650
Look who's here.

457
00:21:02,680 --> 00:21:03,680
Who is here?

458
00:21:07,000 --> 00:21:09,280
Welcome, Drillmaster!

459
00:21:24,320 --> 00:21:25,080
Kaizhi,

460
00:21:25,570 --> 00:21:26,810
look who's here.

461
00:21:29,930 --> 00:21:31,990
Why is the drillmaster bowing to him?

462
00:21:35,930 --> 00:21:37,530
Hello, Drillmaster Hirata.

463
00:21:37,810 --> 00:21:38,610
Hello, madam.

464
00:21:39,650 --> 00:21:40,520
Hello.

465
00:21:41,000 --> 00:21:42,730
Deputy Commander Yang Kaizhi.

466
00:21:44,280 --> 00:21:46,410
He's now the Director of Cavalry.

467
00:21:46,620 --> 00:21:47,250
No.

468
00:21:49,410 --> 00:21:50,440
As a rival,

469
00:21:51,490 --> 00:21:52,810
I respect him more

470
00:21:53,370 --> 00:21:55,370
for his actions at the Yanji border.

471
00:21:55,640 --> 00:21:57,050
What I did back then

472
00:21:57,570 --> 00:21:59,170
was purely out of duty.

473
00:21:59,930 --> 00:22:01,130
No need to bring it up.

474
00:22:01,590 --> 00:22:05,110
I've kept up with your news.

475
00:22:06,170 --> 00:22:08,570
I heard you're drafting

476
00:22:08,930 --> 00:22:12,280
your army's first cavalry outline.

477
00:22:14,680 --> 00:22:15,480
That's right.

478
00:22:16,460 --> 00:22:17,680
Kaizhi is still the same

479
00:22:17,680 --> 00:22:19,170
as back in school—

480
00:22:19,720 --> 00:22:22,030
no horse under him, no man on horseback.

481
00:22:27,640 --> 00:22:29,810
Did you get in touch with Huang Fusheng?

482
00:22:29,810 --> 00:22:31,810
He said he rented a shop

483
00:22:31,830 --> 00:22:33,280
on Dongzhimen Outer Street.

484
00:22:33,280 --> 00:22:34,680
I haven't seen the place yet.

485
00:22:34,680 --> 00:22:36,480
Keeping it all mysterious, huh?

486
00:22:37,930 --> 00:22:40,170
I'm not very familiar with those people.

487
00:22:40,170 --> 00:22:41,000
Tianbai hasn't been

488
00:22:41,000 --> 00:22:42,620
in much contact with them
in the past few years.

489
00:22:42,620 --> 00:22:43,760
It feels distant.

490
00:22:46,760 --> 00:22:49,090
I just came back from the cadet gathering.

491
00:22:50,040 --> 00:22:51,040
Honestly,

492
00:22:51,570 --> 00:22:53,100
I don't feel great about it.

493
00:22:56,090 --> 00:22:57,350
Was Liang Xiang there?

494
00:22:59,330 --> 00:23:00,790
Did he give you a heads-up?

495
00:23:00,890 --> 00:23:01,950
He was avoiding me.

496
00:23:04,510 --> 00:23:06,370
Closeness breeds distance, huh?

497
00:23:06,410 --> 00:23:07,040
Nonsense.

498
00:23:07,680 --> 00:23:10,080
He was afraid
I'd ask him about that matter.

499
00:23:10,460 --> 00:23:11,650
Then that 30,000 yuan of yours

500
00:23:11,650 --> 00:23:12,980
might be down the drain.

501
00:23:16,650 --> 00:23:17,580
I'm telling you.

502
00:23:19,410 --> 00:23:20,870
I think I'm in trouble now.

503
00:23:22,280 --> 00:23:23,940
I don't know how to explain it.

504
00:23:24,200 --> 00:23:25,530
It feels like I'm a thief

505
00:23:26,090 --> 00:23:28,150
and have to take the blame for others.

506
00:23:28,200 --> 00:23:29,200
How do I even ask?

507
00:23:29,610 --> 00:23:31,540
I'm afraid you've got to suck it up.

508
00:23:31,930 --> 00:23:33,590
You're such a refined person.

509
00:23:33,650 --> 00:23:35,650
Why get involved in such a dirty deal?

510
00:23:35,650 --> 00:23:36,280
Shuhong,

511
00:23:36,680 --> 00:23:37,680
I didn't do that

512
00:23:37,680 --> 00:23:38,890
just for myself.

513
00:23:40,000 --> 00:23:42,130
But there's a bit of personal gain too.

514
00:23:42,410 --> 00:23:43,510
As a division commander,

515
00:23:43,510 --> 00:23:45,250
you'll get
carried around in a fancy sedan

516
00:23:45,250 --> 00:23:46,650
and surrounded by guards,

517
00:23:46,650 --> 00:23:47,760
marry five concubines,

518
00:23:47,760 --> 00:23:48,810
and claim a mansion

519
00:23:48,810 --> 00:23:50,410
with gardens front and back.

520
00:23:51,760 --> 00:23:53,620
If I could marry five concubines,

521
00:23:54,010 --> 00:23:55,140
I'd marry you first.

522
00:23:55,200 --> 00:23:55,810
Sure,

523
00:23:55,810 --> 00:23:57,810
as long as you don't mind I have a son.

524
00:23:57,810 --> 00:23:59,170
Dream on.

525
00:23:59,410 --> 00:24:00,280
That would make me a father

526
00:24:00,280 --> 00:24:01,610
before I even get a wife.

527
00:24:03,280 --> 00:24:03,930
Who is it?

528
00:24:04,280 --> 00:24:05,680
Mr. Yang, it's me, Luo Ge.

529
00:24:12,280 --> 00:24:13,280
What is it, Luo Ge?

530
00:24:13,350 --> 00:24:14,280
Here's the thing.

531
00:24:14,280 --> 00:24:15,410
Old Madam

532
00:24:15,410 --> 00:24:16,900
has been feeling a bit lonely at home.

533
00:24:16,900 --> 00:24:17,900
She misses the boy

534
00:24:18,280 --> 00:24:19,170
and is hoping the mother

535
00:24:19,170 --> 00:24:20,760
can bring him over for a visit.

536
00:24:20,760 --> 00:24:21,420
That's all.

537
00:24:21,680 --> 00:24:22,010
Sure.

538
00:24:22,200 --> 00:24:23,410
Tomorrow, I'll have Shuhong

539
00:24:23,410 --> 00:24:24,410
take the boy over.

540
00:24:24,680 --> 00:24:25,680
Great, thank you.

541
00:24:25,890 --> 00:24:27,020
See you another day.

542
00:24:29,200 --> 00:24:30,810
Why did you just agree?

543
00:24:32,400 --> 00:24:34,660
How could I say no
to such a small request?

544
00:24:43,260 --> 00:24:45,670
[Military Advisory Council
Inspection Train]

545
00:24:46,890 --> 00:24:47,490
Nine Dots.

546
00:24:50,570 --> 00:24:51,700
Drillmaster Liang.

547
00:24:52,040 --> 00:24:53,170
Drillmaster Liang.

548
00:24:53,170 --> 00:24:54,570
Come on, let's continue.

549
00:24:56,930 --> 00:24:58,730
Thank you all for your hard work.

550
00:25:07,930 --> 00:25:08,520
Tufang,

551
00:25:09,280 --> 00:25:10,410
how do I look?

552
00:25:11,570 --> 00:25:13,760
Do I look the part
of the reviewing minister?

553
00:25:13,760 --> 00:25:14,930
Look the part?

554
00:25:15,280 --> 00:25:16,280
Zaitao,

555
00:25:16,280 --> 00:25:18,080
you're the reviewing minister.

556
00:25:21,810 --> 00:25:23,200
Just a few moves,

557
00:25:23,760 --> 00:25:25,220
and I'm sweating all over.

558
00:25:25,410 --> 00:25:26,760
Being the reviewing minister

559
00:25:26,760 --> 00:25:28,170
is no easy job.

560
00:25:30,930 --> 00:25:31,860
Listen, once you

561
00:25:32,170 --> 00:25:33,500
get to the 3rd Division,

562
00:25:33,570 --> 00:25:35,170
observe more and speak less.

563
00:25:35,410 --> 00:25:36,570
Don't open your mouth carelessly,

564
00:25:36,570 --> 00:25:38,430
lest you show your inexperience.

565
00:25:39,170 --> 00:25:40,230
When I was in Japan,

566
00:25:40,930 --> 00:25:42,650
the Crown Prince
came to inspect the school.

567
00:25:42,650 --> 00:25:43,810
From start to finish,

568
00:25:43,810 --> 00:25:45,270
he only said three things.

569
00:25:48,040 --> 00:25:48,890
Which three?

570
00:25:48,890 --> 00:25:49,650
Tell me.

571
00:25:52,440 --> 00:25:53,170
Good.

572
00:25:54,280 --> 00:25:54,890
Good.

573
00:25:55,200 --> 00:25:55,810
Good.

574
00:25:58,760 --> 00:26:00,000
I'll do the same.

575
00:26:00,680 --> 00:26:01,670
Whatever I see,

576
00:26:01,810 --> 00:26:03,540
I'll just repeat that one word.

577
00:26:05,040 --> 00:26:05,680
Good.

578
00:26:07,440 --> 00:26:08,090
Good.

579
00:26:08,680 --> 00:26:09,280
Good.

580
00:26:12,040 --> 00:26:13,680
Feels kind of great.

581
00:26:14,490 --> 00:26:15,620
The catch is—

